	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">(8) Any county clerk, circuit clerk, county assessor, prosecuting attorney, or sheriff of a Class I through Class V county, inclusive, any assessor or any sheriff of a Class VI through Class IX county, inclusive, shall devote full time to his or her public duties to the exclusion of any other employment: </span><span class="cs50A3B802">Provided</span><span class="csE736517A">, That any public official whose term of office begins when his or her county&rsquo;s classification imposes no restriction on his or her outside activities may not be restricted on his or her outside activities during the remainder of the term for which he or she is elected.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(9) After July 1, 2025, any serving sheriff who has prior law enforcement experience for the State of West Virginia or any of its political subdivisions shall receive an additional $1,000 of salary for each year of such prior law enforcement experience.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to increase the salary for sheriffs.</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


